body:
@ash211 @markhamstra @rxin Thank you for your comments.
I agree with using `LongType` for `CountDistinct`, `ApproxCountDistinctMerge` and `ApproxCountDistinct`.
I will modify them.

@etrain Given our default 'maxBins' setting of 100, a maximum cardinality of 7 for a categorical features is supported in the 'check for all' strategy. Also, the number of splits in the 'check for all' strategy will always be lower than the bin size.

We will have to use a heuristic if we support more than 10 categorical values. I am fine with using entropy (as @srowen suggested) -- a reference will be great if we can find one. 

It's always difficult to find a reference for practical issues since they are harder to publish. :-(

@rxin Thanks!
But notice that current `CountDistinctFunction` uses `HashSet` to count and its `size` is limited in `Int` range, so the problem @ash211 said still exists in `CountDistinct`.
It might be another issue.
